description: For sale: $169,900. Escape to this 1.3 acre piece of north woods paradise on Tom Lake.  This well constructed cabin is ready to be finished to your own personal taste.  Designed to consist of 2 bedrooms, bathroom and a nice great room with lovely views overlooking the lake.  This fully furnished cabin is built on a slab foundation, has a propane furnace for year round usage and there is a lovely covered porch.  The varying 200+ feet of beautiful shoreline accommodates a great dock, excellent swimming hole, and you may even catch a trophy walleye from the dock.  Or you can watch the sunset over the palisades while languishing on the glider perched on the rocky ledge.  A very neat & insulated outhouse is complimented by an outdoor shower with instant hot water. A 8 X 12 shed provides storage for all your fun gear.  With year-round access this is your dream getaway in the making!

description: For sale: $446,000. Classic Log Home-Scenic Moose Valley.  This beautifully crafted log home sits on 81 acres with a mountain-like setting tucked against the high ridges of Moose Valley.  The 4 bedroom home features fine log-home warmth, a large kitchen with hickory cabinets and black granite counter tops, and plenty of space for the family or visitors with 4 large bedrooms.  The cedar logs were locally sourced, with aspen beams.  The large walk-out basement could be finished for even more space. There's a huge, heated 3 stall, 5-door garage with work shop and storage.  There are two historic 1930's cabins used for storage, too!  The land is rolling and varied with high terrain with direct access to the Superior Hiking Trail.  There's even a small creek and old pond.  A hobby farm?  An outdoorsman's retreat?  Or is this your dream home with nearby access to hiking, fishing on Superior or Arrowhead Trail lakes, and miles of state and federal forest to explore, starting just outside your back door.

description: For sale: $749,000. You will be amazed by the quality of this home the moment you step on the Tigerwood of the covered porch!  Stop and notice all the details along the way as you meander through the home, down the stairs to the shores of Lake Superior, and up the path to the enchanted guest cabin, lovingly named "Stonegate North".  The home was built by contractor Glenn Peterson, known for premium craftsmanship.  Attention to detail is an understatement: porcelain tile, engineered wood flooring, half-log siding, double-hung windows framing the views of the northwoods.  This open-concept home is comfortable and elegant.   Hickory cabinets and Corian countertops showcase the kitchen with a center island cooktop, double ovens, and pass-through window to the sunroom--open to the casual dining area, entertaining couldn't be easier!  Your guests will flow into the living room to admire the spectacular Boulder Creek manufactured rock gas fireplace with its bold wood mantel.  The cozy, intimate sunroom is just the place when you're ready for some quiet time--use the sliders to walk out to the patio, or curl up to read a book.  The main floor also boasts two large bedrooms with shared full bath, a 3/4 bath off the kitchen near the laundry area, and a separate family room perfect for hobbies, office area, or game room.  Upstairs you'll find the private oasis of a master suite;  personal loft area overlooking the living area, full master bath with double sinks, walk-in closet, and a private deck to enjoy morning sunshine.  All this plus a huge heated attached garage with room for a workshop, outdoor toys, storage, and vehicles!  Once you've taken in the beauty of this home, walk to the beach, and take in the landscaped yard, then wander across Stonegate Road to an enchanted land known as "Stonegate North".  Ready for you to finish, the guest cabin has all the characteristics of a northwoods wonderland;  covered porch, wooden patio, outdoor stone entertainment area handcrafted with rocks from the property--fire pits and built-in seating complete this magical place.  What are you waiting for?  This place is going to knock your socks off!!

description: For sale: $439,900. Absolutely delightful 2 bedroom, 2 bath Lake Superior gem, with over 300 ft. of meandering shoreline.   Can you imagine sitting on your deck watching the stunning sunsets or just listening to the waves crashing into this magnificent ledge rock shoreline?  Or you could enjoy the property from the comforts of the charming screened-in gazebo, which is only a short walk down the path. The privacy of this property is unequaled with the shoreline forming a secluded bay with beautiful shelf rock.  Inside this quality built, year round cabin, the great room is flanked by a wall of windows inviting the beauty of Lake Superior into the living space. An efficient Vermont Casting Woodstove is nestled up against a native stone covered wall and will keep you warm on those stormy days "when the gales of November come early!"  The custom made kitchen cabinets, like the floors, are all birch and abundant Corian counters provide plenty of work space in the kitchen.  The informal dining space is surrounded by windows and will become a romantic table when the moon is shining over the lake. You will never want to close the shades in the master bedroom because the views are so exceptional; this room is complete with a large closet and private full bathroom. The 2nd bedroom is roomy enough to include an office space, a murphy bed and is adjacent to the second bathroom. Overlooking the great room is a loft with a skylight, designed as a bonus sleeping area.  The laundry/utility room serves as an entry from the back yard, complete with a laundry tub, counter work space, efficient front-load washer & dryer, and a closet making it a great mudroom. Should you want to venture from this peaceful haven you are only minutes away from hiking & ATV trails, groomed cross country ski trails, snowshoeing in winter, and the amazing High Falls.

description: For sale: $479,000. Head East from Grand Marais and the world slows down a bit, head east from Hovland and go way back to a quieter, simpler time on the North Shore.  Bay Breeze is a home on the shores of Lake Superior, boasting an arcing frontage of 500+ feet! The home is elegance combined with a thoughtful floorplan and single-floor living.  Views to the big lake soothe the eye in all the main rooms, and natural light fills and dances on the vaulted ceilings. Family-reunion size deck nestles close to the land for an intimate connection to rock, shore, and water. The master bedroom is spacious with cavernous closet and private bath. Additional bedroom for friends or family. The living room is just so sweet and comfortable with big views to the nor'easters that blow up occasionally.  You'll be snug and cozy in front of the cobblestone fireplace. The dining room fronts the kitchen, both connect well to the Gitche Gumee surroundings. The kitchen can handle whatever you want to throw at it. Perhaps you ran up to Thunder Bay to the Italian market, it's not far.  That's cool, cook up a mess of pasta and sausages. Don't feel like cooking? Head over to the Hovland General Store: tasty vittles there! Grand Portage is close and has lots to explore including the old fort and museum. If you like history, go a bit further to Fort William.  Grand Marais is not far the other direction. The BWCA and Superior Hiking Trail are a beautiful drive up the Arrowhead. Your off and away here, no one will find you if that's your pleasure.  Though, the fiber optic hums along if you want to connect, or Spotify the Wreck of the Edmund Fitzgerald when the Gales of November come early... This home is all comfort and ease.  Wild setting, with a civilized domicile. Current owners have a short term rental following that you can decide to continue. Or not, keep for yourself, friends and family: the getaway, way up North!

description: For sale: $79,900. Are you looking for some acreage, a little cabin and easy, year round access?  This might be the property for you!  This 75 acre parcel is located off of the Irish Creek Road, in the heart of the Arrowhead Trail.  The lot is gently rolling with beautiful trees, including some nice Pine Trees, plus there is a wildlife pond located on the northern portion of the property.  Look for signs of moose, deer, bear, birds and many other animals.  The lot could be easily split since there is over 1/4 of road frontage.  There is a little one bedroom cabin with a loft, perfect for a weekend getaway.  Great location, close to Tom Lake, Devil Fish Lake, Greenwood Lake, Swamp River, McFarland Lake & the BWCAW for many excellent fishing options.  OR you can spend the day hiking on the Border Route or Superior Hiking Trail, both are close by the property.  OR jump on the dedicated ATV trail, which is just down the road.  The area is also abundant with DNR and USFS Roads that are convenient for mountain biking.

For sale: $225,000. Lot size 1.47 acre. Large cabin is cedar logs. 2 bedrooms, bath is a wash room, with bucket shower, sink, porta pottie for ladies or kids.  Small cabin is an A frame one room with a loft, sleeps 4. Great for extra people, when large cabin is full.  Storage shed and small storage shed on top of hill.  Sauna with changing area.  New outhouse (2015), complient with county codes.  Dock is fixed and very sturdy.  Boat ramp for when boat not in use.  Cabin comes mostly furnished. Generator and small solar unit included. Household items, etc. are negotiable.  
Visitors welcome anytime.  If we are not there, look around.

description: For sale: $159,900. Cottage Home Across From Lake Superior.  This cute home sits just across the highway from the big lake shoreline.
